---
/**
 * ETF - /etf/
 * Product long-form page. Built from the V4 wireframe (Figma node 995:6857),
 * rendered entirely through the shared design system: standardised .hero,
 * alternating sec-light / sec-tint sections, .product-page_table, .row-2 / .card,
 * check-cards and FaqAccordion. Two content patterns unique to this page -
 * the numbered process flow and the icon "types" grid -
 * live in the scoped <style> block and bind to tokens only (rule 2 + rule 9).
 *
 * Nested route → BaseLayout / component imports at ../../ depth.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/site/Breadcrumb.astro';
import FaqAccordion from '../components/sections/FaqAccordion.astro';
import { faqPageSchema } from '../lib/seo';

// FAQs - ETF investing. First three are the wireframe questions; the rest add
// the depth every product page carries (for the FAQPage JSON-LD + SEO).
const FAQS = [
  {
    q: 'What is an ETF in simple terms?',
    a: 'An ETF is a fund that holds a basket of securities and trades on the exchange just like a regular share, throughout market hours. Buying one unit gives you diversified exposure to everything the fund holds - an index, gold, or a sector - in a single trade.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is an ETF safe to invest in?',
    a: 'ETFs are SEBI-regulated, transparent and hold a diversified basket, which generally makes a broad index ETF lower-risk than a single stock. That said, an ETF is a market-linked product - its value moves with the underlying assets and returns are never guaranteed.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I do a SIP in ETFs?',
    a: "Yes - but unlike a mutual fund SIP it isn't an automatic bank auto-debit. You, or a scheduled-order tool, place a recurring manual buy order each interval from your trading account.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Do I need a demat account to buy ETFs?',
    a: 'Yes. ETF units are held in electronic form, so a demat and trading account is required. Mutual funds, by contrast, can be held without a demat account.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How are ETFs taxed in India?',
    a: 'Taxation depends on the underlying asset. Equity ETFs follow equity rules - STCG at 20% under 12 months and LTCG at 12.5% above ₹1.25 lakh. Gold and other non-equity ETFs are taxed differently, and debt ETFs bought on or after 1 April 2023 are taxed at your income-tax slab rate regardless of holding period.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the expense ratio of an ETF?',
    a: 'Most passive Indian ETFs charge roughly 0.05%–0.50% a year, far lower than the 0.50%–2.25% typical of an actively managed equity mutual fund - a meaningful difference over a long horizon once compounding is factored in.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the minimum amount to invest in an ETF?',
    a: 'As little as the price of a single unit - often a few hundred rupees - plus applicable charges. There is no fixed minimum beyond one unit.',
  },
];

const seo = {
  title: 'ETF Investing - Exchange Funds',
  description:
    'Diversify your portfolio with ETFs tracking indices, sectors & commodities. Trade with low expense ratios via Shriram Financial Services.',
  path: '/etf/',
  jsonLd: [faqPageSchema(FAQS.map((f) => ({ question: f.q, answer: f.a })))],
};
---

<BaseLayout seo={seo} mainClass="rev-rise-scale">
  <!-- ================= HERO (standardised, rule 7) ================= -->
  <section class="hero" id="sec-hero" data-section="hero">
    <Breadcrumb trail={[{ name: 'Products', href: '/products/' }, { name: 'ETFs' }]} />
    <div class="hero-inner" data-enter>
      <h1>Invest in <span class="g">Exchange Traded Funds</span> in India</h1>
      <p class="lead">An ETF is a basket of securities that trades on NSE/BSE like a stock - combining mutual-fund diversification with stock-like liquidity. Invest in 100+ ETFs across equity, gold, debt, sectoral and international categories with a SEBI-registered broker backed by 40+ years of trust.</p>
      <div class="cta"><a class="btn-gold" href="/open-demat-account/">Open Demat Account</a></div>
      <div class="hero-feats">
        <div class="feats">
          <div class="feat"><span class="tk" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M4.5 10.5 8 14l7.5-7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span class="lb">&nbsp;SEBI-registered</span></div>
          <div class="feat"><span class="tk" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M4.5 10.5 8 14l7.5-7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span class="lb">&nbsp;100+ ETFs</span></div>
          <div class="feat"><span class="tk" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M4.5 10.5 8 14l7.5-7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span class="lb">&nbsp;Low expense ratio</span></div>
          <div class="feat"><span class="tk" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M4.5 10.5 8 14l7.5-7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span class="lb">&nbsp;Live exchange pricing</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= WHAT IS AN ETF ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-light" id="sec-what" data-section="what" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center" data-enter="2">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">What Is an ETF? - Meaning &amp; Definition</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">An ETF is a basket of securities that trades on NSE/BSE like a stock - pooling investor money into a fund that mirrors an index, with units traded live on the exchange. Unlike a mutual fund, which is priced once daily, an ETF trades like a stock all day.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="row-2" data-reveal-row>
      <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-h">Traded like a stock</h4>
        <p class="card-p">Units are listed on the exchange and bought or sold at live market price throughout the trading day, settling into your demat account.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-h">Mostly passive, low-cost</h4>
        <p class="card-p">Most ETFs are passively managed to track an index, which keeps ongoing costs low. A demat account is needed to hold the units.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= HOW ETFs WORK ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-tint" id="sec-how" data-section="how" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">How ETFs Work - Creation &amp; Redemption Mechanism</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Behind the scenes, an Authorised Participant keeps an ETF's market price anchored to the value of the securities it holds.</p>
    </div>
    <ol class="flow" data-reveal-row>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">1</span><p class="flow-tx">Authorised Participant (AP) assembles the underlying securities basket.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">2</span><p class="flow-tx">Fund house issues ETF units to the AP in exchange for the basket (&ldquo;creation&rdquo;).</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">3</span><p class="flow-tx">Units are listed and traded on NSE/BSE like any other share.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">4</span><p class="flow-tx">Investors buy and sell freely at the live market price.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">5</span><p class="flow-tx">An iNAV published intraday keeps the price anchored to fair value.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">6</span><p class="flow-tx">The AP redeems units for the underlying basket, balancing supply and demand.</p></li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= TYPES OF ETFs ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-light" id="sec-types" data-section="types" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">Types of ETFs Available in India</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">From broad equity indices to gold, bonds, sectors and global markets - a category for almost every goal and risk appetite.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="etf-types" data-reveal-row>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 20V10M10 20V4M16 20v-6M22 20H2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span>
        <h4>Equity ETF</h4><p>Nifty / Sensex</p>
      </div>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"></circle><path d="M12 8v8M10 10.5a1.8 1.8 0 0 1 3.5.6c0 1.2-1.5 1.6-1.5 1.6M12 8V6.5M12 17.5V16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></span>
        <h4>Gold / Silver</h4><p>Physical bullion</p>
      </div>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M7 3h7l4 4v14H7z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M14 3v4h4M10 13h5M10 16.5h5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span>
        <h4>Debt / Bond</h4><p>G-secs, T-bills</p>
      </div>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 9l8-5 8 5M5 9v9M12 9v9M19 9v9M3 21h18" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span>
        <h4>Sectoral</h4><p>Banking, IT</p>
      </div>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"></circle><path d="M3 12h18M12 3c2.5 2.5 3.8 5.7 3.8 9S14.5 18.5 12 21c-2.5-2.5-3.8-5.7-3.8-9S9.5 5.5 12 3z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span>
        <h4>International</h4><p>Nasdaq 100</p>
      </div>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M6 4v6M6 14v6M12 4v3M12 11v9M18 4v9M18 17v3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round"></path><circle cx="6" cy="12" r="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"></circle><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"></circle><circle cx="18" cy="15" r="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7"></circle></svg></span>
        <h4>Smart beta</h4><p>Factor-based</p>
      </div>
      <div class="etf-type">
        <span class="ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M8 6h13M8 12h13M8 18h13M3.5 6h.01M3.5 12h.01M3.5 18h.01" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span>
        <h4>Index ETF</h4><p>Passive replication</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= ETF vs MUTUAL FUND ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-tint" id="sec-vs" data-section="vs" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">ETF vs Mutual Fund - Key Differences</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Both pool your money into a diversified basket - the difference is how they trade, what they cost and how you hold them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="t-scroll"><div class="product-page_table t3 bordered">
      <div class="cell th"><p>Parameter</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>ETF</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Mutual Fund</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Trading Hours</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Real-time, all day</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">End-of-day NAV</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Expense Ratio</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">0.05%–0.50%</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">0.50%–2.25%</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Demat Needed</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Yes</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">No</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">SIP</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Manual / scheduled order</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Auto-debit</p></div>
    </div></div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= HOW TO INVEST ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-light" id="sec-invest" data-section="invest" style="gap:56px;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px;width:100%">
      <h2 class="sec-title">How to Invest in ETFs with Shriram</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">Six steps from account opening to your first ETF trade - and tracking it thereafter.</p>
    </div>
    <ol class="flow" data-reveal-row style="width:100%">
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">1</span><p class="flow-tx">Open a demat account with PAN, Aadhaar and bank details.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">2</span><p class="flow-tx">Activate your linked trading account.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">3</span><p class="flow-tx">Search the ETF ticker on the trading platform.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">4</span><p class="flow-tx">Place a buy order - at market or a limit price.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">5</span><p class="flow-tx">Units are credited to your demat account on T+1.</p></li>
      <li class="flow-step"><span class="flow-num">6</span><p class="flow-tx">Track your holdings and NAV via the app.</p></li>
    </ol>
    <a class="btn-gold" href="/open-demat-account/" style="align-self:center">Start Buying ETFs</a>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= ETF SIP ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-tint" id="sec-sip" data-section="sip" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">ETF SIP - Can You Do a Systematic Investment in an ETF?</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Yes - but unlike a mutual fund SIP, it isn't an auto-debit. You, or a scheduled-order tool, place a recurring manual order each interval.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="t-scroll"><div class="product-page_table t3 bordered">
      <div class="cell th"><p>Parameter</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>ETF SIP</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>MF SIP</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Minimum Investment</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Price of 1 unit</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">₹100–500</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Demat</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Required</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Not required</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Execution</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Manual / scheduled order</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Automatic bank auto-debit</p></div>
    </div></div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= CHARGES & EXPENSE RATIO ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-light" id="sec-charges" data-section="charges" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">ETF Charges &amp; Expense Ratio - What You Actually Pay</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">A handful of small, transparent costs - most of them a fraction of what an actively managed fund charges.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="t-scroll"><div class="product-page_table t3 bordered">
      <div class="cell th"><p>Cost</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Description</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Range</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Expense Ratio</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Annual fund-house fee</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">0.05%–0.50%</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">STT</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Sell-side exchange tax</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">0.001%</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Impact Cost</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Bid-ask spread slippage</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Varies</p></div>
    </div></div>
    <p class="sec-lead">Put together, the total cost of owning a passive Nifty 50 ETF can work out to roughly 0.10%–0.30% a year, compared to 1%–2.25% for an actively managed equity mutual fund - a meaningful difference over a long horizon once compounding is factored in.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= TAXATION ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-tint" id="sec-tax" data-section="tax" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">ETF Taxation - LTCG, STCG &amp; How to File</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">ETF taxation in India depends on the underlying asset class:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="t-scroll"><div class="product-page_table t3 bordered">
      <div class="cell th"><p>ETF Type</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Treatment</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Rate</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Equity ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">STCG &lt; 12mo / LTCG ≥ 12mo</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">20% / 12.5% above ₹1.25L</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Gold ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">LTCG after 24mo</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">12.5%</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Debt ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Taxed any holding period (post-2023)</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Slab rate</p></div>
    </div></div>
    <div class="card">
      <p class="card-p" style="font-style:italic"><strong>Important:</strong> the Finance Act 2023 removed indexation for debt mutual funds and ETFs bought on or after 1 April 2023 - gains are taxed at your income slab regardless of holding period.</p>
      <p class="card-p" style="margin-top:16px">Capital gains from ETF sales must be reported under &ldquo;Capital Gains&rdquo; in your ITR, with equity and non-equity gains disclosed separately. Keep records of purchase price, sale price and holding period for each transaction.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= TOP ETFs ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-light" id="sec-top" data-section="top" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">Top ETFs to Consider - Nifty 50, Gold, Banking &amp; More</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">Rather than a definitive ranking, here's a curated look at category-leading ETFs worth considering, based on AUM, cost and trading liquidity:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="t-scroll"><div class="product-page_table t3 bordered">
      <div class="cell th"><p>Category</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Example</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>AUM / ER</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Nifty 50 ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Tracks Nifty 50</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">High AUM, low ER</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Gold ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Tracks gold price</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">High AUM, low ER</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Banking ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Tracks Bank Nifty</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Mod. AUM, low ER</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">IT ETF</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Tracks Nifty IT</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Mod. AUM, low ER</p></div>
    </div></div>
    <p class="sec-lead">When comparing ETFs within the same category, prioritise lower tracking error, higher AUM for liquidity and a tighter bid-ask spread over chasing the highest recent return.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= PORTFOLIO CONSTRUCTION ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-tint" id="sec-portfolio" data-section="portfolio" style="gap:56px;align-items:center;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px;width:100%">
      <h2 class="sec-title">ETF Portfolio Construction - How to Build a Passive Portfolio</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">ETFs are versatile building blocks for a low-cost, diversified portfolio. Two model approaches, from simple to more advanced:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="row-2" data-reveal-row style="width:100%">
      <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-h">Beginner: 3-ETF portfolio</h4>
        <div class="stack" style="gap:12px">
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Nifty 50 ETF (60%)</strong> - core equity exposure</p>
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Gold ETF (20%)</strong> - inflation hedge</p>
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Debt ETF (20%)</strong> - stability and income</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-h">Advanced: core-satellite</h4>
        <div class="stack" style="gap:12px">
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Core</strong> - Nifty 50 ETF (40%)</p>
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Satellite</strong> - Midcap ETF (20%)</p>
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Satellite</strong> - International ETF (20%)</p>
          <p class="card-p"><strong>Satellite</strong> - Gold ETF (20%)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Your ideal mix depends on age, goals and risk appetite - younger investors with a longer horizon can typically afford a higher equity allocation, while those nearing a goal may tilt toward debt and gold for stability.</p>
    <a class="btn-gold" href="/open-demat-account/" style="align-self:center">Build Your Portfolio</a>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= RISKS ================= -->
  <section class="section stack sec-light" id="sec-risks" data-section="risks" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">Risks of Investing in ETFs - What to Watch Out For</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">ETFs are generally a lower-cost, transparent way to invest, but like any market-linked product they carry risks worth understanding:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="t-scroll"><div class="product-page_table t3 bordered">
      <div class="cell th"><p>Risk</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Description</p></div><div class="cell th"><p>Mitigation</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Tracking Error</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Return may deviate from the index due to fees and rebalancing lag</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Choose ETFs with low historical tracking error</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Liquidity Risk</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Thinly traded ETFs may have wide bid-ask spreads</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Prefer ETFs with higher volume and AUM</p></div>
      <div class="cell tb"><p class="k">Market Risk</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Value moves with the underlying asset class</p></div><div class="cell tb"><p class="v">Diversify across asset classes, stay long-term</p></div>
